item.title: Which ips go where for port forwarding
item.dc:creator: @sasquiotch sasquiotch
item.description:
@sasquiotch wrote:

open command prompt typ ipconfig hit enter… enter your ip in you adress bar… the user is blank password is admin when it asks … go to applications and gaming for application name put moparscape for both ports put 43594 udp and tcp are both selected en enable it … save and close… clcik start - control panel intenet connections net work connections right click your network connection and click properties click settings at the bottom you should see add… click it serveice put moparscape both ports are 43594tcp is selected and the ip is your internal ip u can view that by doing ip config on the command promp… click ok and your ready to go thats port forwarding
